<h2 id="200">3. Redistributing items</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Now, proceed as described below to redistribute items with plentyWarehouse.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Use labels for storage locations</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To use the <strong>Redistribution</strong> function most conveniently, create a label for each storage location and place it at the storage location. This way, you can scan the barcode on the label with your device and access the respective storage location for the redistribution easily in plentyWarehouse.
Have you not created labels for storage locations yet? Refer to the <a href="/en/stock-management/setting-up-a-warehouse#800">Setting up a warehouse</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Redistributing items:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="/en/stock-management/plentywarehouse/installation-and-initial-setup#300">Log into plentyWarehouse</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the menu icon (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-bars  "></i></span>) in the top left corner.<br>
<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-map-signs  "></i></span> <strong><em>Or:</em></strong> Find the <strong>Redistribution</strong> tile in the <strong>Functions</strong> area on the dashboard.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <strong>Redistribution</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="material-sync_alt"></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a search criterion.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> Tap on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-undo  "></i></span> to reset the data you have entered, if necessary.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <strong>Search</strong> (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The variations that correspond to the search criteria are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the variation that should be redistributed.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> If only one search result is found, the variation is opened automatically.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the storage location of the variation.<br>
The source storage location of the variation, a quantity field and a list of target storage locations is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Edit the quantity of variations that should be redistributed.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> If you are using a scanner, scan the item label several times to increase the quantity.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the target storage location to which the stock should be redistributed.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> If you have labelled your storage locations, scan the storage location label instead. To do so, begin by tapping on the field <strong>Barcode</strong> before using your Bluetooth scanner.<br>
→ The items are redistributed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
